<doc id="594748" wikidata="Q6391626" url="?curid=594748" title="Kent Brewster">
<text>Kent Brewster (born 1961) is a writer, editor, and publisher. He was the publisher and frequent editor of the Hugo Award-nominated &quot;Speculations&quot;, a magazine of science fiction and other speculative fiction, from its inception in 1994 until it ceased operating in 2008.

Brewster&#x27;s short story, &quot;“In the Pound, Near Breaktime,&quot; was a finalist for the 1996 Nebula Award for Best Short Story.

Brewster was born in the UK but lives and works in Silicon Valley, as an engineer for Pinterest. His web-based prototypes and demonstrations include Badge Any Feed with Pipes, Blog Juice and Netflix Widgets.

