<doc id="594757" wikidata="Q7575331" url="?curid=594757" title="Speculations (magazine)">
<text>Speculations was a resource for writers in the subgenres of science fiction, fantasy, and other speculative fiction subgenres. Founded in 1994 as a print magazine, &quot;Speculations&quot; moved online in 2000 and ceased operations in 2008. &quot;Speculations&quot; was a Hugo Award for Best Semiprozine nominee seven times. Kent Brewster was the publisher.

Editors included Kent Brewster, Susan Fry and Denise Lee.

